It is only 250 meters to the top of the volcano, which rises to 2,386 meters of altitude, but the exhausted carriers take more than 40 minutes to ascend by turtle pass, keeping the balance and temptingly measuring their steps so as not to slip and fall down the cliff.
They know that any transplant could cost them their lives, as happened to a French tourist who took off years ago because of the risks of Kawah Ijen.
