End Unasur Summit without making public the Lima Declaration
The Sixth Presidential Summit of the South American Union of Nations (Unasur) concluded today in Peru without the publication of the Lima Declaration, previously announced and theoretically signed by the seven attending presidents.
Efe repeatedly attempted to access the document signed at the Sixth Ordinary Meeting of Heads of State and Government of Unasur, but sources of Chancellery and Presidency pointed out at an early stage that they were going to hand it over after the closure, but then claimed that at some point it would be posted on the Peruvian Government's website.
