And remember that evil is good for those of apocalyptic mentality.
And he's not the only teacher who offers courses on the "end of the world" this semester, theoretically the last in history.
In Temple, Assistant Professor Barry Vacker is teaching the course "Media, Culture and the End of the World".
Each week, students explore apocalyptic topics such as nuclear war, zombies, viruses and germs, and global warming.
"We analyze why these ideas proliferate over time," he said, and how they offer hypothetical scenarios that guide certain human behavior.
If nuclear material falls into the hands of terrorists, for example, a war could erupt.
This month the students analyzed films with apocalyptic themes and explored how they compare with real life examples.
"I have tried to inform students about what is possible, probable, credible and impossible," Vacker said.
